(Photo: Getty Images)Have you applied for jobless benefits in the past several weeks and been denied?
It expands jobless benefits to nearly everyone put out of work, including part-time workers, contractors and the self-employed.
Doug Ducey also expanded eligibility benefits by waiving the usual one-week waiting period and requirement that people getting jobless benefits continue to look for work.
Many people are denied because they don't have sufficient earnings history to qualify for state benefits.
People who already were receiving state benefits and filed a weekly certification on Sunday indicating they still were out of work had the $600 in additional federal benefits added to their account starting Monday.